commit_message:
Remove references to puppet-openstack from README

The README references to the retired puppet-openstack module
should be removed, as they link to the empty github page.

This patch also cleans up a few other parts of the README,
such as adding a link to the keystone wiki and removing
'%example' from the installation command to match the
other projects.

Change-Id: Ie74ca8a1914cbb2d3de199001b33ced181501a45
Closes-bug: #1518589

commit_message:
Add --names option for 'role assignment list'

The --names option will try to switch the ID value with
the NAME of the entity.

This patch only covers the display of role names.

Change-Id: I302c73fcb40f3134e20695e6dd543025f34e3169
Partial-Bug: #1479569

commit_message:
OpenStackConfig provider

This patch add support for parsing configuration files of projects
which use oslo.config.cfg.MultiStrOpt (currently Neutron LBaaSv2).

For details see:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.config/api/oslo.config.cfg.html#oslo.config.cfg.MultiStrOpt

Change-Id: If782aa4bf83712ac2a5f4d2f4e8ace782409182d

commit_message:
Make argument params of list methods consistent

The argument type "params" is not consistent between list methods of
services client. This patch makes them consistent.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I539291f86fc85013ead4195a78ed722ac794eaa6

commit_message:
Adjust primary bifrost settings for Debian jessie support

Specific settings are required for Debian jessie as it uses
different defaults from wheezy.

Additionally, we're going to attempt to ensure that the service
folder exists if we're using a systemd template upon install
as sometimes that folder may not be present on systems.

Added genisoimage as a fallback to mkisofs in configuration
drive generation.

Change-Id: I74bf93416513094293bc071fd40e62f4240d61bc
Closes-Bug: 1522552

commit_message:
Make live_migrate_server() use common method

There is a common method action() for calling action API.
This patch makes live_migrate_server() use it for cleanup.

Change-Id: I5d1d23d3a6e4f7efa6e3119db3a2f393c3e4fe69

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-12-03 19:51:12.000000000', 'message': 'Add VM creation support on Debian jessie

Debian jessie changed the libvirt service name from the prior
release and as such we need additional logic to load the defaults
and a defaults file that represents jessie.

Change-Id: I48a64f61d8ba42f76c2df3b984d3090b68e3cf93
Partial-Bug: 1522552
'}, {'created': '2015-12-09 15:05:29.000000000', 'message': 'Add VM creation support on Debian jessie

Debian jessie changed the libvirt service name from the prior
release and as such we need additional logic to load the defaults
and a defaults file that represents jessie.

Additionally, we need to ensure that we start the default network
as it may not be started by default on Debian jessie.

commit_message:
Add VM creation support on Debian jessie

Debian jessie changed the libvirt service name from the prior
release and as such we need additional logic to load the defaults
and a defaults file that represents jessie.

Additionally, we need to ensure that we start the default network
as it may not be started by default on Debian jessie.

Change-Id: I48a64f61d8ba42f76c2df3b984d3090b68e3cf93
Partial-Bug: 1522552

commit_message:
Support of PyMySQL driver for MySQL backend

Add the ability to use python-pymysql library as backend for MySQL
connections.

Update acceptance tests to use pyMySQL.

Change-Id: Id1f036b475e85f208fd906c3a79ce08535f05ac2
Docs: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/PyMySQL_evaluation

commit_message:
Support of PyMySQL driver for MySQL backend

Add the ability to use python-pymysql library as backend for MySQL
connections.

Update acceptance tests to use pyMySQL.

Change-Id: Ia47aa99ade73ae63da0e00e32a4f87cefaaa9bda
Docs: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/PyMySQL_evaluation

commit_message:
Support of PyMySQL driver for MySQL backend

Add ability to use python-pymysql library
as backend for MySQL connections.
Update acceptance tests to use pyMySQL.
Docs: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/PyMySQL_evaluation
The same implementation as it's done for keystone:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/242134/

Change-Id: I730fa419d02ac3910143080121ba19f8be770198

commit_message:
Default Rabbit port to 5672

The default port for rabbitmq is 5672.

This patch makes puppet-mistral use the same
defaults as other puppet openstack modules.

Change-Id: I80d897c8c88158de2cd7ac8c3e88c92395188615

commit_message:
Fix database_connection variable in db_spec

Currently the default for the database_connection variable in
manifests::db is sqlite, but the spec expects it to be mysql.
This results in errors when initial commits of projects are
put up for review. This patch changes the expected db connection
to sqlite.

Change-Id: Ifa9675d0772f5076bcf60f1a7de6f1fbc69ed354

commit_message:
Remove qpid messaging support

Qpid messaging driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1]
Therefore, we cannot support it anymore.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: I87f9e1ee9d8190a2fec6fc5c72885a5c52121cd9

[{'created': '2015-11-12 14:11:04.000000000', 'message': '[inspector] Specify SELinux type context for tftp dir

We create a /tftpboot/ dir in the root directory without
specifying a SELinux type context, so it gets default_t. The
tftp process is not allowed read permission on default_t, and
as a result the ironic-inspector-dnsmasq service fails to
start.

The fix is to specify a type context of tftpdir_t when
creating the /tftpboot/ directory.

Change-Id: Id20802b457a8c75d8b1af04a2d2f56b6b776536e

commit_message:
[inspector] Specify SELinux type context for tftp dir

We create a /tftpboot/ dir in the root directory without
specifying a SELinux type context, so it gets default_t. The
tftp process is not allowed read permission on default_t, and
as a result the ironic-inspector-dnsmasq service fails to
start.

The fix is to specify a type context of tftpdir_t when
creating the /tftpboot/ directory.

This patch also pulls the /tftpboot/ directory out of the if
block relating only to tftp configuration. The /tftpboot/
directory is also used by iPXE/http for the undionly.kpxe
chainloading image.

Change-Id: Id20802b457a8c75d8b1af04a2d2f56b6b776536e
Closes-Bug: 1515630

add more settings to glance api, registry, rabbitmq

scrub_time
signing_dir
token_cache_time

image_cache_max_size

commit_message:
Revert "Fix Ironic DVR configuration"

This reverts commit 46610aacba2396ccd1b931b9c48c66754be15188.

DVR is not working with Ironic yet.
Bug: #1522364 is not fixed.
Changes in Neutron side should be done first.

commit_message:
Add support for RabbitMQ connection heartbeat

Kilo oslo.messaging added heartbeating support for RabbitMQ
connections.  This patch adds support for this in Puppet modules
by managing the oslo_messaging_rabbit/heartbeat_timeout_threshold
and oslo_messaging_rabbit/heartbeat_rate settings.

Closes-bug: 1467667
Change-Id: I3aef101e3a099bcbd96ee32efa7c5f849e6000cf
(cherry picked from commit 8e4068031037e60646525c37de512c0ffe4443a7)

commit_message:
Pin puppet-swift due to duplicate declaration

Puppet-swift changed to resource-like class declaration in one spot,
preventing us to declare the swift::storage::account etc. classes
too. The planned fix is to rollback to the include-like style. We'll pin
for the time being.

Change-Id: Iff49ee9720db9514fb2ab82d870470bdb5073327
Related-Bug: #1524381

(1 comment)

Status report: I'm trying to enable this new IsolatedOVSFixture on a new testscenario of neutron.tests.functional.agent.test_ovs_lib, and I'm running into a conflict between the system's openvswitch and the tests'. For example:

 $ sudo service openvswitch stop
 $ sudo ovs-vsctl --db=unix:/tmp/tmpziAlbj/tmpHaTrRv/db.sock add-br test
 $ ip a | grep test
    9777: test-br57363106: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST> mtu 1500 qdisc noop state DOWN group default 
    9778: test: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST> mtu 1500 qdisc noop state DOWN group default 
 $ sudo service openvswitch start
    Redirecting to /bin/systemctl start  openvswitch.service
 $ ip a | grep test
 $

Basically, the test works (kinda - still need to add references to the isolated ovs we spawn across the code), but once we start another ovs, it deletes interfaces it does not know.

See [1] for a similar problem people ran into and how I got to this. I'm still trying to find a workaround.

[1]: http://openvswitch.org/pipermail/discuss/2015-February/016599.html"}, {'account_id': 12444, 'date': '2015-11-05 14:38:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Also, as per last comment, see: http://openvswitch.org/pipermail/discuss/2014-May/014042.html and the response he got.'}, {'account_id': 8873, 'date': '2015-11-10 16:13:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Just had a conversation with John, John will look into this issue more deeply and try to figure out root cause and a solution.'}, {'account_id': 12444, 'date': '2015-11-11 07:29:49.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 12444, 'date': '2015-11-11 07:37:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

(4 comments)

Newest revision fixes some of the comments I've made, and added some more tests. Specifically, neutron/tests/functional/agent/test_ovs_lib.py:OVSLibIsolatedTestCase.test_isolated_bridges fails consistently (even when the system's openvswitch is stopped) and narrows down the problem significantly.

By turning on ovs-vswitchd's logs (pass -vfile:dbg instead of -vfile:info produces the likes of [1]) shows that ultimately the port is deleted (I believe) by [2], as a result of using some kind of a running index on each created port.

I still need to see exactly which running index this is, and whether I can override it when creating the port. If so, it would seem that this might work after all.

[1]: http://pastebin.com/6hgiX3rm
[2]: https://github.com/openvswitch/ovs/blob/master/vswitchd/bridge.c#L743"}, {'account_id': 12444, 'date': '2015-11-11 07:37:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-11 09:07:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

If you start ovs in a namespace, and that ovs creates a bridge, do you see it in that namespace or the root namespace? If it's created in the ovs-namespace, that has a bunch of implications..."}, {'account_id': 8873, 'date': '2015-11-24 15:08:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

I mean when you execute 'ip a' for example, not ovs-vsctl list-br."}, {'account_id': 12444, 'date': '2015-11-24 15:09:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

They appear in the namespaces:

 $ sudo ip netns exec test-d34aa593-d30c-4c58-b5c5-ca0977c7ed9b ip a
 1: lo: <LOOPBACK,UP,LOWER_UP> mtu 65536 qdisc noqueue state UNKNOWN group default 
    link/loopback 00:00:00:00:00:00 brd 00:00:00:00:00:00
    inet 127.0.0.1/8 scope host lo
       valid_lft forever preferred_lft forever
    inet6 ::1/128 scope host 
       valid_lft forever preferred_lft forever
 2: ovs-system: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST> mtu 1500 qdisc noop state DOWN group default 
    link/ether de:6a:e8:e9:75:2f brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
 3: test-br52102477: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST> mtu 1500 qdisc noop state DOWN group default 
    link/ether 5e:f6:17:a4:43:4a brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff'}, {'account_id': 8873, 'date': '2015-11-24 15:14:26.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

OK, we'd need to map out such usages of the OVS agent. Does it ever rely on the Linux network static 'ip a', 'ip link', etc outside of OVS commands to make decisions. One way would be to just do it and see what happens :) Introduce the ovs-agent test-only conf value for the OVS connection string and change fullstack so that it uses these fixtures, connects them up properly (The centralized bridges would use their own ovs fixture, and be connected via veth devices across namespaces) and passes the correct connection strings to each agent.

I'm also not convinced the openflow will work correctly, that should be checked within the context of this patch. I mean, when I do ovs-ofctl dump-flows <br>, it looks for <br> in *some* openvswitch database... How do you tell it which one?"}, {'account_id': 12444, 'date': '2015-11-24 15:17:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

re: openflow, it looks in some shared folder for the correct unix socket and then uses it, so it doesn't seem to pose an issue at all."}, {'account_id': 12444, 'date': '2015-12-10 17:08:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

The current proposed solution includes putting the (ovsdb-server, ovs-vswitchd) pair of processes in a dedicated namespace. However, ovs developers implied to me that support for this will be dropped in the next version so we're not going to go this way.

They are working on adding proper support for this [1], but until this is done this should be held back.

[1]: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1285005"}, {'account_id': 8873, 'date': '2015-12-10 17:15:39.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

It looks like this isn't properly supported by OVS. Putting this in the freezer until the RHBZ John linked is fixed. Shame =/"}]

commit_message:
WIP: Enable OVS tests isolation

Allow tests to spin up their own openvswitch instance,
guaranteeing test isolation (Each openvswitch instance
uses its own database). This is primarily an enabler
for of_lib functional testing.

WIP/To-Do:
* Document OVS server fixture

Follow up:
* Use it in fullstack
* Decide what functional tests may benefit from this

Change-Id: I86362f46ed86c56ab26c692e64e00567f5ae9960

commit_message:
Remove references to puppet-openstack from README

The README references to the retired puppet-openstack module
should be removed, as they link to the empty github page.

This patch also adds a link to the Cinder wiki to match the
other projects.

Change-Id: Ib6bed22a2cd152c9b9471e5fba0926774606d707
Closes-bug: #1518589

commit_message:
Use whitespace for cinder type-list check.

Hyphens will be matched as a word boundary, so use whitespace to
avoid false positives. For example, with an exisiting "demo-type1"
we can't create a new "type1".

Change-Id: I1167d3e870d1834f57f5cf64ab5cf796344de027

commit_message:
Replaced private field in get_session/engine with public method

We use private field _factory to get access to the oslo.db
method 'get_legacy_facade()'. It's not quite right and
it could be fixed with the help of the new version of oslo.db.

Closes-Bug: #1516963

Change-Id: I3c5726fdb77a7ab9709f2b1951b673f802c66920

Since "network delete" could delete more than one network,
add a (s) to the doc.

commit_message:
Trivial: Do not use plural format in command parameter in "network delete"

Since "network delete" could delete more than one network,
add a (s) to the doc.

And also, rename the parameter "networks" to "network".
The naming style is not using plural format in parameter.

Change-Id: Id434ea905af34457f84ea6bcb18addef5800429a

commit_message:
Keep lines that are commented out once

This patch takes all lines starting with a single # (ignoring lines
starting with '##') and inserts them before the yaml is dumped.  The
intended use case is for those that comment out lines during upgrade
/ maintence to not loose that information.

Change-Id: Ic4b2c45ec0820cf1a01a6d459216d1da89e542cd
Closes-Bug: 1483788

commit_message:
Pass environment variables of proxy to tox

When a development environment is under a proxy, tox is failed even if
environment variables of the proxy are set.

This patch fixes this problem.

Change-Id: Ibde388f69e0e6bdc19900e770989d63f0d5f21dd
Closes-bug: #1524824

commit_message:
Tidy up - Primitive

Some Python class and packages need to be renamed
for a better compliance with the shared terminology
which provides a better understanding of Watcher
objects and components by every contributor.

This patchset is there to change
Primitive to Primitives.
Add BasePrimitive.

Partially implements: blueprint glossary-related-refactoring

Change-Id: I839bddd12b5320b338b2f207d74963afa23de522

commit_message:
Rename Command to Action

Some Python class and packages need to be renamed
for a better compliance with the shared terminology
which provides a better understanding of Watcher
objects and components by every contributor.

This patchset is there to change Command to Action

Partially implements: blueprint glossary-related-refactoring

Change-Id: Id38e133fc8b789319c7db5712d3820ecca1bd51d

commit_message:
Remove brackets from portal

In case IPv6 address is present in location os_brick would fail to
get correct path as brackets are forbidden chars in udev and are removed.

Closes-Bug: #1449492

commit_message:
Removed py33, pypy support

As Openstack Liberty now targets Python 2.7 and 3.4,
we should drop Python 3.3 support from our setup.cfg

Change-Id: I8c8f9222fcf1111e99a943976aae9c5b427f7ee4
Closes-Bug: #1523983

commit_message:
Added ACL tests

Added tests to show the impact of ACL's on container consumers.
Added several edge case ACL tests to verify ACLs do not
override RBAC

Change-Id: Ia503a7abf32640260babb693c94c051e478f7b65
